Disabling upgrades can be done via editing the `enderio.cfg` file in the `config/enderio` folder.

For quick editing, do the following:

- open the file with an editor
- press CTRL+F (or the key combo whcih enables you to do fulltext search)
- enter "upgrades"
- notice the line `S:disabled=`
- add the upgrades you wish to disable behind the `=`, for instance: `endrio:tnt,enderio:speedBoost`. You can enter _any_ upgrade here, both armor and tool upgrades are accepted.
- save the file


ID table:

| Name           | ID                     | 
| -------------- | ---------------------- | 
| direct         | enderio:direct         | 
| travel         | enderio:travel         | 
| storage        | enderio:inv            | 
| spoon          | enderio:spoon          |
| speed          | enderio:speedBoost     |
| sound detector | enderio:soundDetector  |
| padding        | enderio:padding        |
| night vision   | enderio:nightVision    |
| jump height    | enderio:jumpBoost      |
| hoe            | enderio:hoe            |
| glider         | enderio:glide          |
| swim           | enderio:swim           |
| explosive      | enderio:tnt            |
| elytra         | enderio:lytra          |
